The paper presents a novel approach for autonomous navigation of aerial drones using deep Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) and regressors. This falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO) as it involves the automation of drone navigation. The use of CNNs for visual input processing suggests computer vision (cs.CV) as another likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of data augmentation, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.AI) and deep learning (cs.LG). Finally, the system is designed to replace human operators and enhance accuracy of GPS-based map navigation, which suggests the sub-category of control systems (cs.SY).
